\lim_{x\to2}\frac{ax^2-b}{x-2}=4
a,b?
 \lim_{x\to 2}ax^2-b=\lim_{x\to 2}\frac{ax^2-b}{x-2}\cdot (x-2)=4\cdot 0=0, 
 4a-b=0. 
a=1
b=4
 \frac{ax^2-b}{x-2}=\frac{ax^2-4a+4a-b}{x-2}=a\frac{x^2-4}{x-2}+\frac{4a-b}{x-2}=a(x+2)\to 4a, 
\lim_{x \to 2} \frac{ax^2 - b}{x-2} = \lim_{x \to 2} \frac{(\sqrt{a}x + \sqrt{b})(\sqrt{a}x - \sqrt{b})}{x-2} = 4
\sqrt{a}=1
\sqrt{b}
\lim_{x \to 2} \sqrt{a}x + \sqrt{b} = \sqrt{a} \cdot 2 + \sqrt{b} = \sqrt{1} \cdot 2 + \sqrt{4} = 2 + 2 = 4
a=1
b=4
